    { question: "MAC address spoofing mein attacker kya karta hai?", options: ["MAC address delete karna", "Apna MAC address change karna taki kisi aur device ki identity le sake", "MAC address encrypt karna", "MAC address internet pe upload karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "MAC address hardware mein hota hai lekin software se change ho sakta hai (macchanger tool Linux mein). Attacker legitimate device ka MAC spoof karke: MAC filtering bypass karo, network pe unauthorized access lo, ya forensics mein source chhupao." },
    { question: "Promiscuous mode network interface mein kya enable karta hai?", options: ["Faster data transfer", "Interface apne liye nahi intended traffic bhi capture kare — packet sniffing ke liye zaroori", "WiFi mode enable karna", "Firewall bypass"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Normal mode = sirf apne MAC address ke liye packets accept karo. Promiscuous mode = sab packets capture karo, chahe destination koi bhi ho. Wireshark/tcpdump yahi use karta hai. Shared network pe bhi doosro ka traffic dekh sakte ho (hub pe toh definitely, switch pe sirf ARP poisoning ke baad)." },
    { question: "LAN aur WAN mein main difference kya hai?", options: ["LAN wireless, WAN wired hota hai", "LAN limited area (ek building/campus), WAN geographically distributed network (internet bhi WAN hai)", "LAN slow, WAN fast", "LAN public, WAN private"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "LAN (Local Area Network) = limited geography — office, ghar, campus. WAN (Wide Area Network) = cities, countries — internet sabse bada WAN hai. MAN = Metropolitan Area Network (ek city). Attacker pehle local LAN attack karta hai, phir WAN se connect karta hai." },
